author: COMSOL
description:
This example demonstrates how to model transient electroless deposition of copper using mixed potential theory. The model accounts for mass transport by diffusion and electrochemical reactions at the electrode surface. The equilibrium potentials of partial electrochemical reactions are concentration dependent and the mixed potential is evaluated by setting the total current to 0.

The change in current density, deposition thickness, concentration of ionic species during the electroless deposition is computed against time in this example.
label: cu_electroless_deposition.mph
